        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 9:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 916 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Inland Lake, or near Springville. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oneonta, Springville, Cleveland, Ashville, Locust Fork, Allgood,
Fairview, Inland Lake, Highland Lake, Whitney Junction, Easley, St.
Clair Springs, Holly Springs, Caldwell, I 59 Rest Areas At Oneonta,
Remlap, and Clear Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
